    • createTablePrinter

      TablePrinter createTablePrinter(StringBuffer sb, Consumer<TablePrinter.Builder> builder)
      Factory method to create TablePrinter instances.
      Parameters:
      sb - StringBuffer to collect table content.
      builder - initialize table at creation with columns, widths and alignment.
      Returns:
      TablePrinter instance.

    • printCustomer

      StringBuffer printCustomer(StringBuffer sb, Customer customer)
      Print attributes of one Customer object into StringBuffer as column-separated line. 
       Example:
 | 892474 | Meyer, Eric                    | eric98@yahoo.com, (030) 3945-642298          |
      Parameters:
      sb - StringBuffer that will contains the formatted result. A new StringBuffer is created when sb is null.
      customer - Customer object.
      Returns:
      StringBuffer that contains formatted result (same sb).

    • printCustomers

      StringBuffer printCustomers(StringBuffer sb, Collection<Customer> customers)
      Print collection of Customer objects into StringBuffer as lines with Customer attributes. 
       Example:
 | 643270 | Bayer, Anne              | anne24@yahoo.de, (030) 3481-23352   |
 | 412396 | Blumenfeld, Nadine-Ulla  | +49 152-92454                       |
 | 892474 | Meyer, Eric              | eric98@yahoo.com, (030) 3945-642298 |
      Parameters:
      sb - StringBuffer that will contains the formatted result. A new StringBuffer is created when sb is null.
      customers - collection of Customers (null argument is ignored).
      Returns:
      StringBuffer that contains formatted result (same sb).
